children.raw: This was exactly what I told my fiance I wanted - classic and with one large diamond.  I didn't want one of those giant rings with diamond sticking out all over the place.  The solitaire is so much more elegant.  He listened better than I thought - as shown by this ring.  I'm very happy with it. Thanx!

children.raw: A real pretty ring. I'm very pleased with it. I had a little trouble choosing the right diamond simply because there were so many, so I had to learn about color, clarity, depth, table, all that diamond stuff - polish etc., it was all a whirlwind. The learning pages on Zoara sort of helped, but I had to stop at jewelry stores and just ask about this stuff from flesh and blood people. In the end I came back here because the prices were just so much better than the other venues I encountered. My ring arrived very quickly.

children.raw: I was really strapped for cash when I was looking for an engagement ring and I didn't expect to find something so affordable online.  I called Zoara because I didn't believe this was really the price.  After they confirmed the price and answered a few questions I had related to shipping, I bought it. I gave it to my fiance and is quite happy with it.

children.raw: This is everything i was looking for in an engagement ring for my girl. Classy, elegant, traditional but bold at the same time. I went for a .5 carat diamond, couldn't get that exact caratage but got pretty close to it (the .5 didn't have the color or table I was looking for) and it fits the setting quite nicely. I'm not only pleased with Zoara, but with my own diamond selection skill. Maybe they just make me look good. Guys, if you're confused by all the options out there - go with this safe bet.

children.raw: I was all over the place when I first found this site and I really had no idea what I wanted other than that it should be a good quality at a good price. A lady named Sara stayed on the phone with me for 20 minutes going over options and the plusses and minuses. In the end, since I wasn't willing to do so much research we decided it would be best if I went for a good diamond simple design and I'm happy with it.

children.raw: This was exactly what I told my fiance I wanted - classic and with one large diamond.  I didn't want one of those giant rings with diamond sticking out all over the place.  The solitaire is so much more elegant.  He listened better than I thought - as shown by this ring.  I'm very happy with it. Thanx!

children.raw: A real pretty ring. I'm very pleased with it. I had a little trouble choosing the right diamond simply because there were so many, so I had to learn about color, clarity, depth, table, all that diamond stuff - polish etc., it was all a whirlwind. The learning pages on Zoara sort of helped, but I had to stop at jewelry stores and just ask about this stuff from flesh and blood people. In the end I came back here because the prices were just so much better than the other venues I encountered. My ring arrived very quickly.

children.raw: I was really strapped for cash when I was looking for an engagement ring and I didn't expect to find something so affordable online.  I called Zoara because I didn't believe this was really the price.  After they confirmed the price and answered a few questions I had related to shipping, I bought it. I gave it to my fiance and is quite happy with it.

children.raw: This is everything i was looking for in an engagement ring for my girl. Classy, elegant, traditional but bold at the same time. I went for a .5 carat diamond, couldn't get that exact caratage but got pretty close to it (the .5 didn't have the color or table I was looking for) and it fits the setting quite nicely. I'm not only pleased with Zoara, but with my own diamond selection skill. Maybe they just make me look good. Guys, if you're confused by all the options out there - go with this safe bet.

children.raw: I was all over the place when I first found this site and I really had no idea what I wanted other than that it should be a good quality at a good price. A lady named Sara stayed on the phone with me for 20 minutes going over options and the plusses and minuses. In the end, since I wasn't willing to do so much research we decided it would be best if I went for a good diamond simple design and I'm happy with it.

children.raw: This was exactly what I told my fiance I wanted - classic and with one large diamond.  I didn't want one of those giant rings with diamond sticking out all over the place.  The solitaire is so much more elegant.  He listened better than I thought - as shown by this ring.  I'm very happy with it. Thanx!

children.raw: A real pretty ring. I'm very pleased with it. I had a little trouble choosing the right diamond simply because there were so many, so I had to learn about color, clarity, depth, table, all that diamond stuff - polish etc., it was all a whirlwind. The learning pages on Zoara sort of helped, but I had to stop at jewelry stores and just ask about this stuff from flesh and blood people. In the end I came back here because the prices were just so much better than the other venues I encountered. My ring arrived very quickly.

children.raw: I was really strapped for cash when I was looking for an engagement ring and I didn't expect to find something so affordable online.  I called Zoara because I didn't believe this was really the price.  After they confirmed the price and answered a few questions I had related to shipping, I bought it. I gave it to my fiance and is quite happy with it.

children.raw: This is everything i was looking for in an engagement ring for my girl. Classy, elegant, traditional but bold at the same time. I went for a .5 carat diamond, couldn't get that exact caratage but got pretty close to it (the .5 didn't have the color or table I was looking for) and it fits the setting quite nicely. I'm not only pleased with Zoara, but with my own diamond selection skill. Maybe they just make me look good. Guys, if you're confused by all the options out there - go with this safe bet.

children.raw: I was all over the place when I first found this site and I really had no idea what I wanted other than that it should be a good quality at a good price. A lady named Sara stayed on the phone with me for 20 minutes going over options and the plusses and minuses. In the end, since I wasn't willing to do so much research we decided it would be best if I went for a good diamond simple design and I'm happy with it.

children.raw: This was exactly what I told my fiance I wanted - classic and with one large diamond.  I didn't want one of those giant rings with diamond sticking out all over the place.  The solitaire is so much more elegant.  He listened better than I thought - as shown by this ring.  I'm very happy with it. Thanx!

children.raw: A real pretty ring. I'm very pleased with it. I had a little trouble choosing the right diamond simply because there were so many, so I had to learn about color, clarity, depth, table, all that diamond stuff - polish etc., it was all a whirlwind. The learning pages on Zoara sort of helped, but I had to stop at jewelry stores and just ask about this stuff from flesh and blood people. In the end I came back here because the prices were just so much better than the other venues I encountered. My ring arrived very quickly.

children.raw: I was really strapped for cash when I was looking for an engagement ring and I didn't expect to find something so affordable online.  I called Zoara because I didn't believe this was really the price.  After they confirmed the price and answered a few questions I had related to shipping, I bought it. I gave it to my fiance and is quite happy with it.

children.raw: This is everything i was looking for in an engagement ring for my girl. Classy, elegant, traditional but bold at the same time. I went for a .5 carat diamond, couldn't get that exact caratage but got pretty close to it (the .5 didn't have the color or table I was looking for) and it fits the setting quite nicely. I'm not only pleased with Zoara, but with my own diamond selection skill. Maybe they just make me look good. Guys, if you're confused by all the options out there - go with this safe bet.

children.raw: I was all over the place when I first found this site and I really had no idea what I wanted other than that it should be a good quality at a good price. A lady named Sara stayed on the phone with me for 20 minutes going over options and the plusses and minuses. In the end, since I wasn't willing to do so much research we decided it would be best if I went for a good diamond simple design and I'm happy with it.

children.raw: This was exactly what I told my fiance I wanted - classic and with one large diamond.  I didn't want one of those giant rings with diamond sticking out all over the place.  The solitaire is so much more elegant.  He listened better than I thought - as shown by this ring.  I'm very happy with it. Thanx!

children.raw: A real pretty ring. I'm very pleased with it. I had a little trouble choosing the right diamond simply because there were so many, so I had to learn about color, clarity, depth, table, all that diamond stuff - polish etc., it was all a whirlwind. The learning pages on Zoara sort of helped, but I had to stop at jewelry stores and just ask about this stuff from flesh and blood people. In the end I came back here because the prices were just so much better than the other venues I encountered. My ring arrived very quickly.

children.raw: I was really strapped for cash when I was looking for an engagement ring and I didn't expect to find something so affordable online.  I called Zoara because I didn't believe this was really the price.  After they confirmed the price and answered a few questions I had related to shipping, I bought it. I gave it to my fiance and is quite happy with it.

children.raw: This is everything i was looking for in an engagement ring for my girl. Classy, elegant, traditional but bold at the same time. I went for a .5 carat diamond, couldn't get that exact caratage but got pretty close to it (the .5 didn't have the color or table I was looking for) and it fits the setting quite nicely. I'm not only pleased with Zoara, but with my own diamond selection skill. Maybe they just make me look good. Guys, if you're confused by all the options out there - go with this safe bet.

children.raw: I was all over the place when I first found this site and I really had no idea what I wanted other than that it should be a good quality at a good price. A lady named Sara stayed on the phone with me for 20 minutes going over options and the plusses and minuses. In the end, since I wasn't willing to do so much research we decided it would be best if I went for a good diamond simple design and I'm happy with it.

children.raw: This was exactly what I told my fiance I wanted - classic and with one large diamond.  I didn't want one of those giant rings with diamond sticking out all over the place.  The solitaire is so much more elegant.  He listened better than I thought - as shown by this ring.  I'm very happy with it. Thanx!

children.raw: A real pretty ring. I'm very pleased with it. I had a little trouble choosing the right diamond simply because there were so many, so I had to learn about color, clarity, depth, table, all that diamond stuff - polish etc., it was all a whirlwind. The learning pages on Zoara sort of helped, but I had to stop at jewelry stores and just ask about this stuff from flesh and blood people. In the end I came back here because the prices were just so much better than the other venues I encountered. My ring arrived very quickly.

children.raw: I was really strapped for cash when I was looking for an engagement ring and I didn't expect to find something so affordable online.  I called Zoara because I didn't believe this was really the price.  After they confirmed the price and answered a few questions I had related to shipping, I bought it. I gave it to my fiance and is quite happy with it.

children.raw: This is everything i was looking for in an engagement ring for my girl. Classy, elegant, traditional but bold at the same time. I went for a .5 carat diamond, couldn't get that exact caratage but got pretty close to it (the .5 didn't have the color or table I was looking for) and it fits the setting quite nicely. I'm not only pleased with Zoara, but with my own diamond selection skill. Maybe they just make me look good. Guys, if you're confused by all the options out there - go with this safe bet.

children.raw: I was all over the place when I first found this site and I really had no idea what I wanted other than that it should be a good quality at a good price. A lady named Sara stayed on the phone with me for 20 minutes going over options and the plusses and minuses. In the end, since I wasn't willing to do so much research we decided it would be best if I went for a good diamond simple design and I'm happy with it.
children.data: I was all over the place when I first found this site and I really had no idea what I wanted other than that it should be a good quality at a good price. A lady named Sara stayed on the phone with me for 20 minutes going over options and the plusses and minuses. In the end, since I wasn't willing to do so much research we decided it would be best if I went for a good diamond simple design and I'm happy with it.

attribs.alt: HTC One M9

children.raw: Read full HTC One M9 review
children.data: Read full HTC One M9 review

children.raw: BoomSound stereo speakers with Dolby Audio
children.data: BoomSound stereo speakers with Dolby Audio

children.raw: improves on the M8 without straying too far from the template. What it does is remedy its predecessor’s shortcomings – the cameras and physical buttons being two of those.
children.data: improves on the M8 without straying too far from the template. What it does is remedy its predecessor’s shortcomings – the cameras and physical buttons being two of those.

children.raw: Gone is the Duo camera of old, in favour of a more traditional 20.7-megapixel main sensor, which is capable of capturing a lot more detail. However, it’s inconsistent and struggles in the dark. On the front is a 4 UltraPixel camera that, as it goes, has excellent low-light credentials.
children.data: Gone is the Duo camera of old, in favour of a more traditional 20.7-megapixel main sensor, which is capable of capturing a lot more detail. However, it’s inconsistent and struggles in the dark. On the front is a 4 UltraPixel camera that, as it goes, has excellent low-light credentials.

children.raw: You’ll be able to admire those snaps on the same 5-inch, 1,920 x 1,080 display as before, though the M9 has slightly thinner bezels. Its front-facing BoomSound stereo speakers with Dolby Audio are clear, loud, and far better than anything else you’ll find on a smartphone.
children.data: You’ll be able to admire those snaps on the same 5-inch, 1,920 x 1,080 display as before, though the M9 has slightly thinner bezels. Its front-facing BoomSound stereo speakers with Dolby Audio are clear, loud, and far better than anything else you’ll find on a smartphone.

children.raw: Design is largely the same, though the power key has been moved from the top edge to the side, for easier access, and the volume buttons have been improved. The M9 is actually 0.02mm thicker than its older brother, but it still feels great in the hand, thanks to the curved, brushed metal back and slimmer bezels. There’s a new raised black square to house the camera too, but we could do without the tacky-looking two-tone trim around the sides.
children.data: Design is largely the same, though the power key has been moved from the top edge to the side, for easier access, and the volume buttons have been improved. The M9 is actually 0.02mm thicker than its older brother, but it still feels great in the hand, thanks to the curved, brushed metal back and slimmer bezels. There’s a new raised black square to house the camera too, but we could do without the tacky-looking two-tone trim around the sides.

children.raw: Android 5.0 Lollipop is the operating system of choice, and the snappy new octa-core Snapdragon 810 processor and 3GB of RAM mean the M9 blasts through complex 3D games and everyday tasks. The battery is a 2,840mAh number, which can just about keep it powered for two days. It’s a very quick charger though, going from flat to full in about an hour and a half.
children.data: Android 5.0 Lollipop is the operating system of choice, and the snappy new octa-core Snapdragon 810 processor and 3GB of RAM mean the M9 blasts through complex 3D games and everyday tasks. The battery is a 2,840mAh number, which can just about keep it powered for two days. It’s a very quick charger though, going from flat to full in about an hour and a half.
